"title": "8718: disobedience",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8718",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The refusal to obey someone, especially someone in a position of authority. Scripture insists on the need to obey God at all times.</p>\n<h2>Disobedience enters people's hearts for various reasons</h2>\n<h3>Disobedience comes through greed and lust</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:6\">GEN 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:11-Gen3:12\">GEN 3:11–3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:19-Exod16:20\">EXO 16:19–16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:20-Josh7:21\">JOS 7:20–7:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:2–11:4</a></p>\n<h3>Disobedience arises from impatience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:23\">EXO 32:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:10-Num20:11\">NUM 20:10–20:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:8-1Sam13:14\">1SA 13:8–13:14</a></p>\n<h3>Disobedience comes through fear</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:2-Jer43:7\">JER 43:2–43:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:13\">JHN 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:42\">JHN 12:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:12\">GAL 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>Disobedience results from pride and arrogance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:1\">LEV 10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:2\">EXO 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:16\">2CH 26:16</a></p>\n<h2>Unbelief is disobedience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:12\">HEB 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:23-Jer7:28\">JER 7:23–7:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:30-Rom11:32\">ROM 11:30–11:32</a> <em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:20\">Ro 11:20</a> makes it clear that the disobedience spoken of here was unbelief</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:18-Heb3:19\">HEB 3:18–3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:2\">HEB 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:6\">HEB 4:6</a></p>\n<h2>Lack of love is disobedience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:24\">JHN 14:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:9\">1JN 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:15\">1JN 3:15</a></p>\n<h2>Disobedience to God leads to punishment</h2>\n<h3>Punishment is applied to individuals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:23-Gen3:24\">GEN 3:23–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:1-Lev10:2\">LEV 10:1–10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:12\">NUM 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:18\">1SA 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:14\">2SA 12:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:10-Jonah1:12\">JON 1:10–1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:5-Eph5:6\">EPH 5:5–5:6</a></p>\n<h3>Punishment for the disobedience of unbelief</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:8-2Thess1:9\">2TH 1:8–1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:2-Heb2:3\">HEB 2:2–2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Nations are also punished</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:14\">GEN 15:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:7\">ACT 7:7</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:26-Deut11:28\">DEU 11:26–11:28</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:15\">1SA 12:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:35\">EXO 32:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15\">DEU 28:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:11\">ISA 13:11</a></p>\n<h3>Disobedience, like all sin, can be forgiven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:19\">ROM 5:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:1-Eph2:5\">EPH 2:1–2:5</a></p>",
